          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "4021 and 4022 are bake element load missing codes — upper/single oven (4021) and lower oven (4022). The control detects that no current is flowing to the bake element when it should be energized. Diagnostic sequence: check the bake element for open circuit (broken internal wire), check the voltage at the element terminals, replace the relay board if both element and voltage check fine. 4121/4122 are the same pattern for the Right Convection element, 4321/4322 for the Left Convection element, 4221/4222 for the Broil element. 4421/4422 are cooling fan load missing. We carry the service documentation for all E Series error codes."
